# Sync architecture

## Upload eligibility

```sql
SELECT * FROM {table} WHERE synced = 0 AND uuid IS NOT NULL AND TRIM(uuid) != ''
```

## Common failures

| Symptom | Likely cause |
|---------|----------------|
| Push tries 100k+ rows | Bloated `change_log` — run `prune-stale-change-log.js` |
| Txn aborted on commit | Too many rows in one Mongo transaction — batch commit in `sync-server/services/commit.js` |
| Row never uploads | Missing `uuid` on insert |
| Stuck unsynced after upgrade | `node scripts/backfill-sync-uuids.js` then Upload |

## Push flow

Tablet `sync-client.push()` → prune journal → build from `synced=0` → HTTP chunks → `commit.js` upsert by `uuid`

Do not re-introduce journal-only changeset builds without filtering `synced=0`.
